<figureCitation box="[246,324,1538,1562]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="11.[151,250,1917,1940]" captionTargetBox="[271,1311,439,1890]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[264,1323,431,1895]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 8. Phlugiolopsis tribranchis sp. nov. A – G. male: A. pronotum in dorsal view; B. apex of abdomen in dorsal view; C. left cercus in dorsal view; D. left cercus in ventral view; E. right cercus in lateral view; F. apex of abdomen in ventral view; G. subgenital plate in ventral view; H – J. female: H. apex of abdomen in lateral view; I. apex of ovipositor in lateral view; J. subgenital plate in ventral view; K. spine-shaped process of subgenital plate in lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/209931/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Figs. 8</figureCitation>
, 
