<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="13" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1436,151,1030]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,869,893]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Remarks.</emphasis>
The new species differs from the known species of the genus 
<taxonomicName box="[1008,1162,869,893]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Phlugiolopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1008,1162,869,893]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Phlugiolopsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by: male cerci trifurcate with 
<number box="[211,225,903,927]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="2.0">2</number>
processes; baso-lateral margin of female subgenital plate with 
<number box="[960,974,903,927]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="1.0">1</number>
small spine-shaped process and 
<number box="[1356,1370,903,927]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="1.0">1</number>
short transverse wrinkle on each side, one third basal area obviously concave.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
